<TEXT>
lebanese authorities have released 
a dutch journalist who spent two months in a beirut jail on 
espionage and drug charges the dutch foreign ministry said 
charles van der leeuw was freed tuesday and accompanied to syria 
by an official from the dutch embassy in damascus a ministry 
spokesman said 
van der leeuw had been detained since sept 28 in what the dutch 
journalists union said was a move to stop him from criticizing the 
lebanese christian army commander gen michel aoun 
the ministry spokesman who asked not to be identified in line 
with ministry policy would not comment on the circumstances of van 
der leeuw release 
