brief nato leaders on the discussions 
the allies were aghast to learn in 1987 that thenpresident 
reagan and gorbachev had come close to a deal at a summit in 
reykjavik to abolish all nuclear weapons in spite of the fact that 
nato regards some of those arms as vital to deter soviet attack 
