over utah weakens 
santa ana winds typically are caused when a highpressure system 
forms over the northern rocky mountain states while a lowpressure 
system hovers over baja california 
air rushing across the western deserts from high to low pressure 
heats up and dries out and then roars through mountain passes 
around the los angeles basin 
