the kremlins latest bid to break a bitter 
territorial dispute between armenia and azerbaijan was met 
wednesday with demonstrations strikes and angry criticism from 
both sides 
on the final day of its fall session tuesday the supreme soviet 
parliament overwhelmingly approved a directive disbanding a special 
commission that had imposed direct rule from moscow on the disputed 
nagornokarabakh territory the territory is located inside 
azerbaijan but the the majority of its population is armenian 
