<TEXT>
convicted killer dalton prejean won a stay of 
his midnight execution wednesday from the us supreme court after 
spending the day with his family in the state prisons death house 
prejean 10 days shy of his 30th birthday had been scheduled to 
die in the electric chair for a murder he committed as a teenager 
but the supreme court granted prejeans emergency plea barring 
his execution until the justices decide whether they will hear his 
formal appeal to set aside his death penalty no date has been set 
for the courts action on the formal appeal 
the supreme court had previously turned down three of his 
appeals 
he was 17 when he shot donald cleveland in the face in 1977 
after being stopped for driving with a broken tail light prejean 
had been freed six months earlier from a juvenile detention center 
where he served time for killing a taxi driver when he was 14 
cleveland was the only louisiana state policeman ever murdered 
while on duty 
prejean would have been the first person executed under the us 
supreme courts june ruling that authorizes executions of people 
who commit capital crimes while they were 16 or 17 
prison officials said his mother wife son brother and 
sisterinlaw were among those authorized to visit him 
prejean on death row in louisiana longer than anyone else 
would have been the 19th person executed in louisiana since the 
supreme court upheld the death penalty in 1976 nationwide 119 
people have been put to death 
on tuesday gov buddy roemer rejected a 32 pardon board 
recommendation that prejeans life be spared and the 5th us 
circuit court of appeals denied a ninth stay of execution 
the 5th circuit said that while prejean had low intelligence 
his intelligence quotient was not low enough to call him retarded 
death penalty opponents made prejeans case a national cause 
celebre saying he should be spared because he was nearly retarded 
an iq of 76 and because he was so young when he killed the 
trooper 
the 5th circuit which rejected prejeans appeal said he is not 
retarded under standards of the american association on mental 
retardation which sets the threshhold at an iq of 70 
in the appeals courts 39page opinion chief judge charles 
clark wrote 
to date 11 different lawyers have represented prejean in the 
processing of 20 legal proceedings in 6 different courts before 35 
different judges the matter is being considered by this panel for 
the third time it is time to let justice be done 
the pardon board on monday recommended commuting the death 
sentence to life in prison after hearing testimony from prejean and 
others about the killers childhood abuse at the hands of his aunt 
his limited mental ability and his remorse over his killings 
roemer however cited the brutal nature of clevelands death 
noted that the victim was a uniformed trooper on duty and said 
prejeans sentence met all judicial standards for the death penalty 
