to see into the future lucky luciano often wouldnt make a move 
without consulting lansky 
lansky saw it as a business drug traffic was something he 
wanted no part of he was also against prostitution he wanted to 
stop at gambling and booze he was a man who could be trusted if 
you played by the rules he could be very dangerous if you stepped 
outside the rules 
the neon empire written by journalistnovelist pete hamill 
also stars gary busey linda fiorentino dylan mcdermott julie 
carmen harry guardino and richard brooks larry peerce directed on 
location in los angeles and arizona 
i play max brower rabbinically said landau like a rabbi 
but a deadly one hes a man you can talk to do business with 
like lansky hes the man who ties the jewish mobs and the italian 
mafia together 
bugsy siegel was a man who was emotionally wild lansky had to 
keep him under control siegel was later killed in los angeles 
landau worked on the neon empire in june and july after 
completing work on woody allens crimes and misdemeanors next 
he worked in by the dawns early light for home box office he 
also stars in max and helen for tnt 
hes probably best remembered as rollin hand the master of 
disguise in the tv series mission impossible his former 
wife barbara bain was cinnamon carter they later starred in the 
syndicated series space 1999 
many people believe that landaus role as dr judah rosenthal in 
crimes and misdemeanors will bring him his second nomination 
for an academy award he was nominated as best supporting actor 
last year for tucker the man and his dreams 
my role is the biggest male protagonist woodys ever written 
outside of his own roles he said he usually writes his own 
role and a role for a female protagonist i dont want to say too 
much about my role but what happens after people see it is 
fascinating it resonates for days afterward ive never been in a 
movie that affects people that powerfully 
landau a native of brooklyn studied art at the pratt institute 
and at the age of 18 became assistant to cartoonist gus edson in 
drawing the gumps he also illustrated billy roses pitching 
horseshoes column 
the gumps was the most popular comic strip in the country at 
one time landau said i drew the lettering and the backgrounds 
for the daily strip the sunday strip had a separate story and i 
did the story and all the drawing from conception to finish you 
could create your own little world in cartooning i could create 
little oneact plays 
nevertheless landau quit after winning an audition to the 
actors studio the only other actor accepted at that time was steve 
mcqueen 
the role in mission impossible was created for landau by 
bruce geller a writer who had studied acting in a class taught by 
landau the character was originally called martin land landau 
thought that was too obvious and geller changed it to martin hand 
the name used in the pilot 
space 1999 came after the star trek series but before 
the star wars movies landau was one of the astronauts on moon 
base alpha who were pushed into outer space when atomic waste 
stored on the moon went critical and acted as a propellant as they 
passed through various solar systems the astronauts kept checking 
for a liveable planet and were checked out in turn by curious 
otherworldly creatures 
the show was created for abc but instead became a pioneer in 
firstrun syndication it inspired norman lear to put mary 
hartman mary hartman into syndication 
after that landau did not have a major film role until 
tucker 
i was working but i was doing mindless pictures he said 
i always believed a good role would come along it did when 
francis ford coppola cast me in tucker 
next he will produce and play a role in the film adaptation of 
kurt vonneguts breakfast of champions 
