hanson plc a british industrial conglomerate 
with large us holdings said wednesday its fourthquarter profit 
fell about 54 percent as a result of onetime factors while 
operating profit was higher 
hansons net profit according to british accounting principles 
fell to 318 million from 685 million in the quarter ended sept 
30 the decline came because of a tax charge in the 1989 quarter 
and large onetime gains on asset sales made in the 1988 quarter 
hanson said profit before taxes and onetime items rose to 520 
million from 444 million 
earnings per american depository receipt on a fully diluted 
basis rose to 44 cents a share from 39 cents a share according to 
british accounting principles in britain earnings per adr are 
calculated on pretax profits before tax and extraordinary 
onetime items 
sales in the quarter rose to 304 billion from 295 billion a 
year earlier 
for the full fiscal year net income fell to 178 billion from 
181 billion because of decreased gains from asset sales profit 
before taxes and onetime items rose to 172 billion from 142 
billion 
