that stockholders not tender common stock to mccaw at this time 
the statement said 
mccaw the nations largest cellular telephone company has 
offered 150 a share for 225 million shares of lin stock an 
amount that would lift its stake in lin to 512 percent 
it has also asked that lin submit its offer to shareholders for 
a vote at the same time as they vote on the linbellsouth deal 
if it refuses mccaw has threatened to mount a proxy fight for 
control of the lin board at the jan 12 meeting 
the lin board set the close of business dec 8 as the record 
date for determining the stockholders entitled to participate in 
mccaws consent solicitation to replace a majority of the board 
should mccaw decide to pursue that course of action 
