varity corps proposed 579 million acquisition 
of kh corp formerly fruehauf corp was approved by kh 
stockholders wednesday the company said 
the sale is the last stage in the dismantling of fruehauf to pay 
debt from a leveraged buyout arranged to fight off a 1986 takeover 
attempt 
khs main holding is kelseyhayes co a producer of aluminum 
wheels and antilock braking systems 
fruehauf changed its name to kh on aug 4 after selling 
maritime operations and the trucktrailer manufacturing business 
that had been its mainstay the trailer business continues as 
fruehauf trailer corp a terex corp subsidiary 
kh corp will become a wholly owned subsidiary of varity 
formerly masseyferguson a torontobased maker of farm and 
industrial machinery 
the transaction could be completed thursday or friday kh 
spokesman david hladik said 
fruehauf borrowed 15 billion in 1986 in a restructuring 
arranged in conjunction with merrill lynch amp co to fend off a 
hostile takeover attempt by investor asher edelman 
weighed down with debt the company ran into illtimed reverses 
in the truck trailer business including increased competition and 
a surge in materials costs such as the price of aluminum hladik 
said 
we ended up selling off all our assets to pay off the debt 
he said 
those included a fleet of 5000 leased trailers a financial 
subsidiary and an aerospace unit 
